===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|ic|nocap=y}}: a hand ({{zh-l|*又}}) using a capturing tool ({{zh-l|*𰅱}}) to hunt a wild boar ({{zh-l|*豕}}). Later, {{zh-l|*𰅱}} was omitted and a redundant component {{zh-l|*口}} or {{zh-l|*甘}} was added (Chen Jian, 2020; Xie Mingwen, 2020). 

The components eventually corrupted into the modern form.

===Etymology===
Compare {{cog|my|ဝံ့|t=to dare}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; STEDT), from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*kV-wam|t=to dare}}, which Schuessler reconstructs as {{m|sit-pro||*k-wam}} to account for the initial velar in the Chinese form.

